This paper involves the use of deep neural networks to predict weather uncertainty, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the modification of the 3D U-Net architecture, which is commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). Additionally, the incorporation of temporal data suggests the use of recurrent neural networks (cs.NE) or sequential decision-making models (cs.SD).
